# HTTP Parameter Pollution (HPP) - Educational Overview

HTTP Parameter Pollution (HPP) is a web security vulnerability where multiple parameters with the same name are sent in a single HTTP request. This can bypass input validation and Web Application Firewall (WAF) rules.

## Understanding HPP

### What is HPP?
HPP occurs when an attacker sends multiple values for the same parameter, which can confuse the application's parsing logic.

### Example of HPP in a Request:
```
GET /search?q=hello&q=world HTTP/1.1
```

